#: src/Infrastructure/FeatureToggles/FeatureToggleService.php:61
msgid "When enabled, players see their own status colour and parents see their child's. When disabled, the status dot is staff-only (coaches, scouts, Head of Development, Academy Admin). The detailed breakdown remains staff-only regardless. Note: a status change can still be inferred indirectly if other surfaces (e.g. evaluations) reveal it; this toggle hides the explicit dot, not the underlying judgement."
msgstr ""

#: src/Infrastructure/FeatureToggles/FeatureToggleService.php:65
msgid "Allow new user registration"
msgstr ""

#: src/Infrastructure/FeatureToggles/FeatureToggleService.php:66
msgid "When enabled, staff can send invitations and invitees can create accounts. Disable to stop all new user creation — new invitations cannot be issued and pending invitations cannot be accepted while disabled. Linking an already-existing WordPress user to a TalentTrack record (silent link when an invitee is already logged in with the matching email) is unaffected."
msgstr ""

#: src/Infrastructure/FeatureToggles/FeatureToggleService.php:87
msgid "This is a demo-only install"
msgstr ""

#: src/Infrastructure/FeatureToggles/FeatureToggleService.php:88
msgid "Enable on pilot / training / ephemeral demo installs where every record is demo data. With this on, demo mode is permanently active: all newly created records auto-tag as demo, demo filtering always shows the tagged set, and the runtime mode toggle is overridden. Disable for production installs where some records are real club data."
msgstr ""

